comments: VanVleet (TOR) brings his hand towards Brunson's (NYK) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Siakam (TOR) applies his forearm to Brunson's (NYK) side and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
The ball makes contact with the wiring above the backboard, and possession is correctly awarded to Toronto.
Siakam (TOR) is firming up over his right leg when marginal contact occurs with Grimes (NYK) during the pick.
VanVleet (TOR) is bracing for the contact from Grimes (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet releases away from the contact.
Anunoby (TOR) brings his forearm towards Brunson's (NYK) front and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Anunoby (TOR) turns into Quickely's (NYK) body and delivers contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) is already in Robinson's (NYK) path and VanVleet absorbs the marginal contact as he turns away from Robinson.
Robinson (NYK) and Siakam (TOR) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs off ball.
VanVleet (TOR) is already in Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as Barrett commits to going under the pick.
Barrett (NYK) is retreating alongside Barnes' (TOR) path and he absorbs the marginal contact in the post.
Randle (NYK) moves forward into Barnes' (TOR) body and initiates contact as he defends the shot near the rim.
Siakam (TOR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Randle (NYK).
Siakam (TOR) moves into Randle's (NYK) space and initiates body contact that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Barrett (NYK) brings his forearm towards Barnes' (TOR) lower body and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) makes simultaneous contact with Robinson's (NYK) arm and the ball as he dislodges the ball.
VanVleet (TOR) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK).
Anunoby (TOR) is firming up over his left leg when contact with Grimes (NYK) occurs during the screen.
Siakam (TOR) is already in Grimes' (NYK) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Barrett (NYK) extends his hand and initiates contact with Barnes' (TOR) arm during his upward shooting motion.
Quickley (NYK) is already in Siakam's (TOR) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Randle (NYK) extends his arms into Barnes (TOR) and dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Barnes (TOR) makes contact with Barrett's (NYK) upper off-arm during his dunk shot that does not affect the speed, quickness, balance and/or rhythm of his shot.
Anunoby (TOR) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) is already in Robinson's (NYK) path when contact occurs during the screen, which he absorbs.
Brunson (NYK) swipes his arm down and initiates contact with Siakam's (TOR) arm as he defends the shot at the rim.
Siakam (TOR) is moving alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) and Anunoby (TOR) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
VanVleet (TOR) steps on the baseline as he attempts to gain possession.
Siakam (TOR) does not maintain verticality and makes contact with Barrett's (NYK) arm as he defends the shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) is already in Randle's (NYK) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Robinson (NYK) is moving alongside Achiuwa's (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs with Achiuwa's off arm after he's removed his hand from the ball.
Achiuwa (TOR) goes to, not through, Robinson's (NYK) space during the driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) legally contests Barnes' (TOR) shot near the rim.
Achiuwa (TOR) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) brings his right hand towards Anunoby's (TOR) upper body and marginal contact occurs as Robinson dislodges the ball from Anunoby.
Anunoby (TOR) legally contests Robinson's (NYK) shot near the rim.
After Robinson's (NYK) missed dunk, the ball makes contact with the equipment above the backboard.  Possession is correctly awarded to Toronto.
Randle (NYK) and Barnes (TOR) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as Randle deflects the ball away from Barnes.
Barnes (TOR) briefly grasps Randle's (NYK) arm and marginal contact occurs as Randle pursues the loose ball.
Barnes (TOR) turns into Randle's (NYK) body and initiates contact as he contests the shot near the rim.
VanVleet (TOR) makes clean contact with the ball as he and Randle (NYK) pursue the rebound.
Randle (NYK) and Barnes (TOR) come together at the same spot in the air and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the rebound.
Achiuwa (TOR) moves forward into Bartett's (NYK) space and initiates contact as he defends the shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) is moving alongside Barnes' (TOR) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Randle (NYK) cleanly dislodges the ball from Trent Jr. (TOR), and the ensuing body contact is incidental.
Barnes (TOR) legally contests Brunson's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
